00:11:56,567 --> 00:11:57,894
好 我们走
{\fs10}Okay, let's go.

183
00:11:59,369 --> 00:11:59,997
我们去哪
{\fs10}Where we goin'?

184
00:12:00,081 --> 00:12:00,816
那边
{\fs10}That way.

185
00:12:01,193 --> 00:12:02,738
好 一起去
{\fs10}Okay, we'll go together.

186
00:12:04,496 --> 00:12:05,346
你没事吧
{\fs10}You okay?

187
00:12:07,054 --> 00:12:08,657
失陪一下
{\fs10}Just excuse me for a second.

188
00:12:11,387 --> 00:12:12,772
我有说错什么吗
{\fs10}Did I say something?

189
00:12:13,574 --> 00:12:15,692
你没有 是那个混蛋汤米
{\fs10}No, that asshole, Tommy did.

190
00:12:17,488 --> 00:12:21,167
她小时候 母亲离开了 如此而已
{\fs10}Her mom left when she was a kid, just like that.

191
00:12:21,660 --> 00:12:23,810
但别人总是念叨
{\fs10}Yeah, people wouldn't stop talking about it, though.

192
00:12:23,894 --> 00:12:25,442
毕竟我们住的是小镇
{\fs10}You know, we live in a small town.

193
00:12:25,530 --> 00:12:27,613
八卦真的很无聊哎
{\fs10}Yeah, the gossip got really mean.

194
00:12:27,699 --> 00:12:28,633
真是的
{\fs10}Jeez.

195
00:12:29,633 --> 00:12:31,080
是啊 但闲言仍缠着她
{\fs10}Yeah, but it still bothers her,

196
00:12:31,166 --> 00:12:33,344
所以我觉得你你逃不过
{\fs10}so I guess that stuff sort of sticks with you.

197
00:12:33,639 --> 00:12:35,991
她唯有我们作朋友了
{\fs10}Yeah, and we're like her only friends now.

198
00:12:42,744 --> 00:12:44,895
我意思 她肯定不是你的菜
{\fs10}So, I would say she's definitely not your type.

199
00:12:44,983 --> 00:12:47,068
丝黛拉 她不是任何人的菜
{\fs10}It's Stella. She's not anyone's type.

200
00:12:47,334 --> 00:12:49,022
不敢苟同
{\fs10}Don't think I'd agree with that.

201
00:12:49,458 --> 00:12:51,672
是个妞你就喜欢 你的话不作数
{\fs10}You like every girl. It doesn't count.

202
00:12:51,916 --> 00:12:53,151
不是每个妞
{\fs10}It's not every girl.

203
00:12:53,235 --> 00:12:55,509
说你有弹簧刀
{\fs10}Tell me you at least you got a switchblade.

204
00:12:56,621 --> 00:12:58,068
可看你的弹簧刀吗
{\fs10}Can I see your switchblade?

205
00:12:58,156 --> 00:13:00,243
我什么时候提过弹簧刀
{\fs10}Did I say I had a switchblade?

206
00:13:00,791 --> 00:13:03,853
你没提 但我猜...
{\fs10}No, I guess you didn't say you had...

207
00:13:04,862 --> 00:13:06,664
他有弹簧刀 - 我知
{\fs10}He has a switchblade. - I know.

208
00:13:13,836 --> 00:13:16,088
今天是万圣节 所以
{\fs10}Well, it is Halloween, so...

209
00:13:17,575 --> 00:13:18,926
你想看鬼屋吗
{\fs10}Do you want to see a haunted house?

210
00:13:37,074 --> 00:13:38,225
你没开玩笑
{\fs10}You weren't kidding.

211
00:13:38,894 --> 00:13:40,179
早说了不会令你失望的
{\fs10}Told you it wouldn't disappoint.

212
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:46,514
在万圣节 这里会不会很热闹
{\fs10}I don't know, you'd think on Halloween, this place would be hoppin'.

213
00:13:46,601 --> 00:13:48,413
以前挺热闹
{\fs10}Oh, it was, for a while,

214
00:13:48,666 --> 00:13:51,114
后来有些孩子失踪 所以被封了
{\fs10}then some kid went missing, so they boarded it up.

215
00:13:51,202 --> 00:13:53,920
我还以为拆了建商场什么的
{\fs10}I think it's being torn down for a mall or something.

216
00:13:55,172 --> 00:13:55,873
大家
{\fs10}Hey, guys.

217
00:14:02,846 --> 00:14:03,963
小丑优先
{\fs10}Clowns first.

218
00:14:04,486 --> 00:14:05,239
是嘛
{\fs10}Really?

219
00:14:20,226 --> 00:14:23,230
既然见到了 我们可以撤了吗
{\fs10}Okay, there, we saw it. Can we go now?

220
00:14:24,077 --> 00:14:25,359
怎么一股弱鸡味
{\fs10}Who ordered the chicken?

221
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:29,530
我不喜欢在死过小孩的屋子里过夜
{\fs10}Because I don't like to spend my nights in a house where a child murderer lived?

222
00:14:29,904 --> 00:14:31,238
那房子里死过人吗
{\fs10}Someone was killed in that house?

223
00:14:32,073 --> 00:14:32,951
太黑了
{\fs10}That's pretty dark.

224
00:14:33,809 --> 00:14:34,823
以前是谁住过
{\fs10}Who lived here?

225
00:14:34,910 --> 00:14:35,757
贝洛斯一家
{\fs10}The Bellows.

226
00:14:35,842 --> 00:14:39,829
19世纪末 首批定居者之一
{\fs10}One of the first families to settle here in the late 19th century.

227
00:14:40,246 --> 00:14:43,532
当时造了造纸厂 小镇因此而闻名
{\fs10}Built the paper mill that pretty much put this town on the map.

228
00:14:46,219 --> 00:14:47,804
至少楼梯还能用
{\fs10}We could at least look for some stairs.

229
00:14:51,987 --> 00:14:52,922
如我所料
{\fs10}Just as I thought.

230
00:14:53,586 --> 00:14:55,757
这地方严不透风
{\fs10}They got this place locked up pretty tight.

231
00:14:56,092 --> 00:14:57,107
谁有笔
{\fs10}Anyone got a pen?

232
00:14:58,861 --> 00:15:01,911
此乃神笔萝拉 她疯狂地爱上了我
{\fs10}Meet Lola. She is madly in love with me.

233
00:15:01,997 --> 00:15:03,382
也许是爱你的手
{\fs10}Yeah, your hand maybe.

234
00:15:03,932 --> 00:15:04,933
好
{\fs10}Nice.

235
00:15:05,299 --> 00:15:06,434
我的萝拉 你干什么
{\fs10}Lola! Hey, what?

236
00:15:18,777 --> 00:15:20,989
他比你神多了
{\fs10}He's so much dreamier than you.

237
00:15:34,859 --> 00:15:36,506
贝洛斯一家有个秘密
{\fs10}The Bellows had a secret:

238
00:15:36,594 --> 00:15:39,578
他们不允许独生女离家
{\fs10}a daughter that they never allowed to leave the house.

239
00:15:39,665 --> 00:15:42,247
传说她确有邪乎
{\fs10}The myth is that there was something really off about her.

240
00:15:42,333 --> 00:15:47,718
而真正的可怕在于 她家人抹去了所有合影中的她
{\fs10}A really scary part is that her family erased her from every single portrait.

241
00:15:47,801 --> 00:15:51,889
直到今天 无人寻到莎拉的照片
{\fs10}To this day, nobody's ever found a picture of Sarah.

242
00:15:57,482 --> 00:15:58,733
他们拒绝承认她
{\fs10}They disowned her.

243
00:16:03,817 --> 00:16:04,799
赶紧跑 小丑 - 妈的
{\fs10}Better run, clown. - Shit!

244
00:16:04,886 --> 00:16:06,029
快跑
{\fs10}Better run!

245
00:16:08,853 --> 00:16:10,836
你肯定抓不到我
{\fs10}Bet you can't catch me!

246
00:16:13,026 --> 00:16:15,877
查克 你敢跳向我 我掐不死你
{\fs10}Chuck, if you jump out at me, I'm going to punch you in the throat.

247
00:16:17,282 --> 00:16:18,622
她后来怎么了
{\fs10}So what happened to her?

248
00:16:19,331 --> 00:16:23,815
孩子们各方聚拢 希望一睹"奇怪的莎拉"
{\fs10}Kids would come from all over in hopes to get a peek at Strange Sarah.

249
00:16:23,903 --> 00:16:25,756
尽管他们没见过她
{\fs10}And though they never saw her,

250
00:16:26,202 --> 00:16:27,820
但能听到她的声音
{\fs10}they could hear her.

251
00:16:28,673 --> 00:16:29,857
透过墙
{\fs10}Through the wall.

252
00:16:31,942 --> 00:16:33,658
莎拉给他们讲故事
{\fs10}Sarah told them stories.

253
00:16:35,145 --> 00:16:36,797
恐怖故事
{\fs10}Scary stories.

254
00:16:40,619 --> 00:16:42,689
有些孩子再也没回家
{\fs10}Some kids never returned home.

255
00:16:42,772 --> 00:16:44,354
镇上的孩子死了
{\fs10}Children around town died...

256
00:16:44,737 --> 00:16:46,356
据说死于中毒
{\fs10}Poisoned, they said.

257
00:16:46,951 --> 00:16:48,902
大家心知肚明是莎拉
{\fs10}Everyone knew it was Sarah.

258
00:16:48,990 --> 00:16:51,739
但在暴徒染指她之前
{\fs10}But before the mob could even get their hands on her,

259
00:16:51,824 --> 00:16:54,860
她便用自己的头发上吊了
{\fs10}she'd already hung herself with her own hair.

260
00:17:06,772 --> 00:17:08,500
和传说一样
{\fs10}And as the legend goes,

261
00:17:08,872 --> 00:17:11,622
如果你在黑暗中来到贝洛斯的家
{\fs10}if you come to the Bellows House at dark,

262
00:17:11,710 --> 00:17:13,503
还让莎拉给你讲故事
{\fs10}and ask Sarah to tell you a story...

263
00:17:14,143 --> 00:17:16,693
这将是你人生最后的故事
{\fs10}...it'll be the last story you ever hear.

264
00:17:27,157 --> 00:17:28,609
这是什么
{\fs10}Oh, what's this?

265
00:17:35,697 --> 00:17:37,068
推开 后面有路
{\fs10}Push the other way.

266
00:17:37,332 --> 00:17:38,318
推
{\fs10}Push.

267
00:17:41,904 --> 00:17:43,220
真的有
{\fs10}No way.

268
00:18:26,274 --> 00:18:27,957
就是这里了
{\fs10}Well, that's it.

269
00:18:50,259 --> 00:18:51,610
莎拉的房间
{\fs10}Sarah's room.

270
00:18:55,163 --> 00:18:57,147
你吓不到我的
{\fs10}You're not going to scare me.

271
00:19:01,803 --> 00:19:02,820
查克
{\fs10}Chuck?

272
00:19:06,407 --> 00:19:07,359
查克
{\fs10}Chuck?

273
00:19:29,361 --> 00:19:30,613
那什么
{\fs10}What the...

274
00:20:06,424 --> 00:20:08,403
什么 老太太呢
{\fs10}What? Where's the old lady?

275
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:10,778
那狗呢
{\fs10}And the dog?

276
00:20:10,865 --> 00:20:11,849
什么老太太
{\fs10}What old lady?

277
00:20:14,816 --> 00:20:15,827
我们赶紧走
{\fs10}We gotta get out of here.

278
00:20:16,867 --> 00:20:19,787
丝黛拉 丝黛拉 我们赶紧走
{\fs10}Stella! Stella! We got to get out of here!

279
00:20:20,104 --> 00:20:21,456
丝黛拉 走吧
{\fs10}Stella, let's go!

280
00:20:22,241 --> 00:20:24,425
大家过来看 快来
{\fs10}Guys, you've gotta see this! Come here.

281
00:20:31,316 --> 00:20:33,164
谁是弱鸡
{\fs10}Who ordered the chicken?

282
00:20:33,250 --> 00:20:34,137
闭嘴
{\fs10}Shut up.

283
00:20:37,887 --> 00:20:39,598
她家人将她禁闭于此
{\fs10}This is where her family kept her.

284
00:20:40,024 --> 00:20:42,060
令她远离世界
{\fs10}Locked her away from the world.

285
00:20:42,491 --> 00:20:44,979
独自一人 宛如怪胎
{\fs10}All alone as some sort of freak.

286
00:20:45,256 --> 00:20:48,645
她的座位一定是这里
{\fs10}She must have just sat right here

287
00:20:49,361 --> 00:20:51,713
透过这堵墙 给孩子们讲故事
{\fs10}and told her stories to the kids through this wall.

288
00:20:53,098 --> 00:20:55,151
我们以前怎么没见过
{\fs10}How have we never seen this before?

289
00:20:56,569 --> 00:20:58,953
是大人不希望
{\fs10}I don't think anyone wanted us to?

290
00:21:21,258 --> 00:21:22,340
现在能撤了吗
{\fs10}Can we get out of here now?

291
00:21:43,399 --> 00:21:44,447
那是什么
{\fs10}What's that?

292
00:21:50,832 --> 00:21:52,168
难以置信
{\fs10}I can't believe it.

293
00:21:53,051 --> 00:21:54,736
这是她的恐怖故事书
{\fs10}It's her book of scary stories.

294
00:21:55,485 --> 00:21:56,565
她有书?
{\fs10}She had a book?

295
00:21:56,653 --> 00:21:59,168
我所听闻的传说 并没有这本书
{\fs10}There's no book in the version of the myth I heard.

296
00:21:59,257 --> 00:22:01,008
每个版本的传说都有这本书
{\fs10}The book is a part of every version of the myth.

297
00:22:01,992 --> 00:22:05,973
而且这是用孩子们的血 书写的
{\fs10}And... that it was written in children's blood.

298
00:22:06,062 --> 00:22:08,243
孩子们听了故事就死了 好吗
{\fs10}Well, kids died hearing these stories, okay?

299
00:22:08,331 --> 00:22:10,345
把书放回原处去
{\fs10}Look, let's put it back where you found it

300
00:22:10,433 --> 00:22:11,514
我们现在就走
{\fs10}and let's just get out of here now.

301
00:22:11,602 --> 00:22:12,982
妈呀
{\fs10}Oh, shit!

302
00:22:13,068 --> 00:22:13,918
我来搞定
{\fs10}I got it, I got it, I got it.

303
00:22:14,004 --> 00:22:14,984
所有人闭嘴
{\fs10}Everybody, okay, everybody just shut up.

304
00:22:15,067 --> 00:22:17,138
坏了 是老太太和狗
{\fs10}Oh, no. It's the old lady and the dog!

305
00:22:18,137 --> 00:22:19,452
汤米 别说了 好吗
{\fs10}Tommy, stop it, okay?

306
00:22:19,540 --> 00:22:20,602
让他们出去
{\fs10}Just let them out.

307
00:22:21,108 --> 00:22:22,522
露西 是你吗
{\fs10}Ruth, is that you?

308
00:22:22,611 --> 00:22:23,857
你能开门吗
{\fs10}Will you open the door?

309
00:22:24,344 --> 00:22:26,899
别开玩笑了 如果你不开门
{\fs10}Joke's over. If you don't open it...

310
00:22:27,917 --> 00:22:29,467
别这样 快 - 我会报告警长的
{\fs10}You can't do this! Come on! - ...I'll tell the Chief.

311
00:22:33,021 --> 00:22:34,805
你干嘛那么做
{\fs10}Why would you do that?

312
00:22:36,056 --> 00:22:38,871
一点也不好笑 汤米 拜托
{\fs10}This isn't funny! Tommy, come on.

313
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:40,812
是我弟弟
{\fs10}It's my little brother.

314
00:22:42,996 --> 00:22:43,946
拜托
{\fs10}Please.

315
00:22:45,095 --> 00:22:46,980
打开该死的门
{\fs10}Open the damn door!

316
00:22:47,631 --> 00:22:48,413
开门
{\fs10}Open it.

317
00:22:48,498 --> 00:22:51,249
露西 下来 放我们出去
{\fs10}Ruth! Down here. Let us out!

318
00:22:56,103 --> 00:22:57,287
反正你够垃圾
{\fs10}You're trash anyway.

319
00:22:59,643 --> 00:23:02,680
汤米 不好意思刚才烧了你的车
{\fs10}Tommy, I'm sorry about the burning shit, man.

320
00:23:03,177 --> 00:23:04,861
希望你们自寻出路
{\fs10}I hope you find a way out.

321
00:23:06,068 --> 00:23:06,897
还好吗
{\fs10}Good?

322
00:23:06,982 --> 00:23:08,060
还好
{\fs10}Yeah.

323
00:23:08,582 --> 00:23:10,464
赶紧拿开 - 你没事
{\fs10}Get it off me! - Oh, you're fine!

324
00:23:10,553 --> 00:23:12,133
把东西从我身上拿开
{\fs10}No! Get it off, get it off me! Get it off me!

325
00:23:13,955 --> 00:23:15,167
把东西从我身上拿开
{\fs10}Get it off me! Get it off me!

326
00:23:15,257 --> 00:23:17,305
你没事 已经拿下来了 - 有东西咬我
{\fs10}You're fine. I got it, I got it. It's fine. - Something's bit me!

327
00:23:17,389 --> 00:23:18,937
你能帮我一把吗
{\fs10}Hey, can you help me with this?

328
00:23:19,025 --> 00:23:20,374
蜘蛛拿掉了 - 谢谢
{\fs10}The spiders are gone. - Thank you.

329
00:23:20,459 --> 00:23:22,610
老天 奥吉 好吧 你真色
{\fs10}Jesus, Auggie. Okay, you're such a horndog.

330
00:23:22,695 --> 00:23:24,942
你先别忙着勃起 帮我们撤退先
{\fs10}Can you lose your stiffy for a second and help us get out of here?

331
00:23:25,030 --> 00:23:26,994
不好笑 有女士在场
{\fs10}Not funny! There's a lady present.

332
00:23:27,500 --> 00:23:29,952
女士们 请吧
{\fs10}Ladies... present.

333
00:23:32,070 --> 00:23:33,351
你得用力推
{\fs10}Come on, come on! You gotta push harder.

334
00:23:33,438 --> 00:23:34,167
加把劲儿
{\fs10}Come on.

335
00:23:40,312 --> 00:23:42,465
莎拉·贝洛斯 给我讲个故事
{\fs10}Sarah Bellows, tell me a story.

336
00:23:45,117 --> 00:23:46,532
给我讲个故事
{\fs10}Tell me a story.

337
00:23:47,247 --> 00:23:49,431
莎拉·贝洛斯 给我讲个故事
{\fs10}Sarah Bellows, tell me a story.

338
00:24:06,667 --> 00:24:07,947
等等 我有听到
{\fs10}Wait, wait, wait. I hear something.

339
00:24:08,034 --> 00:24:09,015
有人来了
{\fs10}Someone's here.

340
00:24:09,101 --> 00:24:10,082
他回来了
{\fs10}He came back.

341
00:24:10,170 --> 00:24:11,219
汤米 - 你...
{\fs10}Tommy! - You got...

342
00:24:11,305 --> 00:24:13,286
我们万分抱歉 - 谢谢
{\fs10}We're sorry, we're real sorry. - Thank you!

343
00:24:13,372 --> 00:24:15,387
我收回我说过的话
{\fs10}I... I take back everything I ever said, man.

344
00:24:15,474 --> 00:24:16,688
对不起 伙计
{\fs10}Sorry, man!

345
00:24:17,211 --> 00:24:19,160
汤米 求你了
{\fs10}Tommy, please!

346
00:24:32,758 --> 00:24:34,505
露西 你约谁不好 非约那个神经病
{\fs10}Ruth, why would you date a psychopath like that?

347
00:24:34,591 --> 00:24:36,176
好过掏粪男孩
{\fs10}Better than fishing for turds.

348
00:24:38,331 --> 00:24:40,144
是谁解开的锁
{\fs10}So, who unlocked it?

349
00:24:40,231 --> 00:24:42,346
管那么多 走人先
{\fs10}Who cares? Let's just get out of here.

350
00:24:42,472 --> 00:24:44,837
漂亮的皮耶罗套装 - 谢谢
{\fs10}Nice Pierrot costume. - Thank you.

351
00:24:45,836 --> 00:24:46,751
看
{\fs10}See?

352
00:24:49,135 --> 00:24:50,186
有意思
{\fs10}Well, that was fun.

353
00:24:53,576 --> 00:24:54,567
<i>湿...</i>

