00:57:04,875 --> 00:57:07,188
救救我
{\fs10}Help me, help me!

705
00:57:07,278 --> 00:57:08,328
露西 我来了
{\fs10}Ruth, I got you.

706
00:57:08,414 --> 00:57:09,595
没事的 我来了
{\fs10}It's okay. It's okay. I got you.

707
00:57:09,680 --> 00:57:11,594
救我 救我 让它们滚
{\fs10}Help me, help me. Get them off!

708
00:57:11,685 --> 00:57:13,205
弄走它们
{\fs10}Get them off!

709
00:57:13,719 --> 00:57:15,998
露西 没事了 我来了
{\fs10}Ruth, it's okay. It's okay. I got you.

710
00:57:16,386 --> 00:57:19,104
把它们弄走 - 你会没事的
{\fs10}Get them off! - You're going to be okay, all right? It's okay.

711
00:57:22,595 --> 00:57:24,111
闪开 闪开 闪开
{\fs10}Move, move, move!

712
00:57:27,764 --> 00:57:30,249
你没事的 没事 露西
{\fs10}You're okay. You're okay, you're okay, Ruthie.

713
00:57:31,199 --> 00:57:32,651
救命 来人帮忙 快
{\fs10}Help! Somebody, get help, now!

714
00:57:40,839 --> 00:57:42,219
你没事 露西 没事
{\fs10}You're okay, Ruthie, you're okay.

715
00:57:42,305 --> 00:57:44,119
都完了 - 把它们弄走
{\fs10}It's all finished. - Get them off, get them off.

716
00:57:44,209 --> 00:57:45,759
都没了了 露西 都没了
{\fs10}They're all gone, Ruthie. They're all gone.

717
00:57:45,846 --> 00:57:47,728
弄走它们
{\fs10}Get them off me. Get them off. Get them off me.

718
00:57:47,813 --> 00:57:49,459
弄走它们 - 露西 都没了
{\fs10}Get them off me! - Ruthie, they're all gone,

719
00:57:49,548 --> 00:57:51,330
都没了 没了 好吗
{\fs10}they're all gone, they're all gone, okay?

720
00:57:51,416 --> 00:57:53,201
弄走它们 - 你没事
{\fs10}Get them off me. - You're okay.

721
00:57:53,719 --> 00:57:55,057
弄走它们
{\fs10}Get them off me.

722
00:58:03,761 --> 00:58:06,613
太猛了 我希望她没事
{\fs10}It's intense. I hope she's okay.

723
00:58:07,631 --> 00:58:09,813
我看见她了 莎拉在那儿
{\fs10}I saw her. Sarah was there.

724
00:58:09,900 --> 00:58:12,115
她控制了整件事
{\fs10}She was controlling the entire thing.

725
00:58:12,702 --> 00:58:14,219
我姐姐走了
{\fs10}My sister's gone.

726
00:58:14,871 --> 00:58:16,087
我们是下一个
{\fs10}We're next.

727
00:58:17,339 --> 00:58:18,556
是我们
{\fs10}We're next.

728
00:58:25,781 --> 00:58:26,731
你找到了吗
{\fs10}You find it?

729
00:58:29,619 --> 00:58:31,136
路易丝·巴普蒂斯特
{\fs10}Louise Baptiste...

730
00:58:32,383 --> 00:58:33,366
卢卢
{\fs10}Lou Lou?

731
00:58:34,585 --> 00:58:35,735
金郡路220号
{\fs10}220 Goldshire Road.

732
00:58:39,589 --> 00:58:41,655
我又做乱梦
{\fs10}I had this messed-up dream again.

733
00:58:42,300 --> 00:58:43,808
我被困在红室
{\fs10}I was trapped in the red room.

734
00:58:43,894 --> 00:58:48,413
有个死白胖女 不停地低声说
{\fs10}And there's that fat, pale lady who keeps whispering,

735
00:58:49,331 --> 00:58:51,481
"在这邪恶之地
{\fs10}"This is an evil place.

736
00:58:51,567 --> 00:58:53,282
趁能跑 先跑"
{\fs10}"Run away while you still can."

737
00:58:56,538 --> 00:58:58,755
我害怕女巫会用它来对付我
{\fs10}I'm scared the witch is going to use it against me.

738
00:59:03,912 --> 00:59:04,793
你好
{\fs10}Hello.

739
00:59:05,226 --> 00:59:07,397
卢卢·巴普蒂斯特还住在这吗
{\fs10}Uh, does Lou Lou Baptiste live here still?

740
00:59:08,716 --> 00:59:12,974
"我不想轰炸任何人 如果不是为了拯救..."
{\fs10}"I don't want to bomb anybody if it's not necessary to save..."

741
00:59:13,320 --> 00:59:16,235
狡猾的迪基 这不是总统的名字(指尼克松)
{\fs10}Tricky Dicky. That's no name for a president.

742
00:59:16,324 --> 00:59:18,475
妈 有客到
{\fs10}Mama, you got company!

743
00:59:32,602 --> 00:59:34,352
卢卢 你听得到我们吗
{\fs10}Lou Lou, can you hear us?

744
01:00:19,546 --> 01:00:21,363
你可能是下一个
{\fs10}You may be the next.

745
01:00:23,016 --> 01:00:24,532
你为什么这么说
{\fs10}Why do you say that?

746
01:00:26,385 --> 01:00:28,301
为什么 因为这曲子 姑娘
{\fs10}Why, that's the song, girl.

747
01:00:29,888 --> 01:00:34,572
永远别笑 因为灵车过去
{\fs10}♪ Don't ever laugh as a hearse goes by

748
01:00:34,656 --> 01:00:36,772
因为你可能会是
{\fs10}♪ For you may be

749
01:00:36,858 --> 01:00:38,842
下一个死去者
{\fs10}♪ The next to die ♪

750
01:00:41,695 --> 01:00:43,378
莎拉喜欢那首歌
{\fs10}Sarah loved that song.

751
01:00:49,336 --> 01:00:50,602
我们有她的书
{\fs10}We have her book.

752
01:00:54,908 --> 01:00:57,190
你找到她的书了 给我
{\fs10}You found her book? Give it here.

753
01:01:11,524 --> 01:01:13,174
我给她的
{\fs10}I give her this.

754
01:01:14,893 --> 01:01:16,873
我为那姑娘悲哀
{\fs10}I feel so sorry for that girl,

755
01:01:16,959 --> 01:01:20,913
她独自坐在黑暗中
{\fs10}sitting down there in the darkness all by herself.

756
01:01:24,735 --> 01:01:26,819
你妈有教过她什么吗
{\fs10}Did your mom ever teach her anything?

757
01:01:28,503 --> 01:01:29,620
教她
{\fs10}Teach her?

758
01:01:30,635 --> 01:01:31,586
黑魔法
{\fs10}Black magic?

759
01:01:33,840 --> 01:01:34,595
没有
{\fs10}No.

760
01:01:35,107 --> 01:01:37,358
不存在魔法 孩子
{\fs10}There is no magic, child.

761
01:01:38,778 --> 01:01:40,731
只有愤怒
{\fs10}There is only rage.

762
01:01:42,113 --> 01:01:44,632
那她怎么还在写故事
{\fs10}Then how is she still writing the stories?

763
01:01:47,519 --> 01:01:48,871
故事伤人
{\fs10}Stories hurt.

764
01:01:50,221 --> 01:01:51,902
故事治人
{\fs10}Stories heal.

765
01:01:52,989 --> 01:01:55,112
你知道你做了什么吗
{\fs10}Do you know what you have done?

766
01:01:55,370 --> 01:01:56,199
做了什么
{\fs10}Done what?

767
01:01:56,962 --> 01:01:59,347
你不该拿走书
{\fs10}You shouldn't have taken the book.

768
01:02:01,666 --> 01:02:03,583
你让她愤怒了
{\fs10}You made her angry.

769
01:02:08,104 --> 01:02:11,888
"虫子爬 虫子爬出来"
{\fs10}"The worms crawl in, the worms crawl out..."

770
01:02:11,975 --> 01:02:13,390
她有时会这样
{\fs10}She gets this way sometimes.

771
01:02:13,478 --> 01:02:14,659
我务必要了解
{\fs10}Look, I need to know.

772
01:02:14,746 --> 01:02:16,695
下次吧 我得安定她
{\fs10}Another time. I need to settle her down.

773
01:02:16,780 --> 01:02:18,929
不 我们务必要了解情况
{\fs10}No, we need to know. I need to know.

774
01:02:19,016 --> 01:02:22,699
她在医院 全都告诉医生了 那姑娘也在那医院上吊的
{\fs10}She told the doctors everything she knew at the hospital where that disturbed girl hung herself.

775
01:02:22,784 --> 01:02:23,798
但我 我以为
{\fs10}But I... I thought...

776
01:02:23,886 --> 01:02:25,566
所有人都说莎拉在家里上吊的
{\fs10}Everyone always said Sarah hanged herself in the house.

777
01:02:25,654 --> 01:02:27,367
你不在场 我妈在场
{\fs10}You weren't there. Mama was.

778
01:02:28,656 --> 01:02:30,145
医院有档案
{\fs10}The hospitals have records.

779
01:02:30,228 --> 01:02:31,475
莎拉的档案
{\fs10}Records of Sarah.

780
01:02:31,721 --> 01:02:34,505
那我们还在这里干什么 走
{\fs10}Then what are we still doing here? Let's go.

781
01:02:37,093 --> 01:02:38,807
今天是选举日 乡亲们
{\fs10}It's election day, folks,

782
01:02:38,896 --> 01:02:41,345
让你的声音被听到
{\fs10}so let your voice be heard.

783
01:02:41,432 --> 01:02:45,407
拒绝战争 拒绝越战
{\fs10}Say no to the war! Say no to Vietnam.

784
01:02:45,737 --> 01:02:49,824
拒绝送我们的孩子去死
{\fs10}Say no to sending our children to die.

785
01:03:22,602 --> 01:03:23,518
劳驾
{\fs10}Excuse me.

786
01:03:24,844 --> 01:03:28,229
我们需要查看一名前患者的档案
{\fs10}We need to see the records of a former patient.

787
01:03:29,605 --> 01:03:31,355
我们不提供患者档案
{\fs10}We don't give out patient records.

788
01:03:34,510 --> 01:03:35,656
好吧
{\fs10}Well, uh,

789
01:03:36,046 --> 01:03:36,993
我是说
{\fs10}I mean,

790
01:03:37,267 --> 01:03:39,996
她大约死于100年前
{\fs10}she died about 100 years ago.

791
01:03:41,017 --> 01:03:43,132
我肯定她或其他人
{\fs10}I'm sure she or anybody else

792
01:03:43,220 --> 01:03:45,541
可能不在乎
{\fs10}probably doesn't care, you know.

793
01:03:46,121 --> 01:03:48,136
为什么你们想查看旧患者档案
{\fs10}Why do you kids wanna look at old patient files for?

794
01:03:48,224 --> 01:03:51,610
学校作业 关于
{\fs10}Uh, for a school assignment on, uh...

795
01:03:53,695 --> 01:03:56,610
人类心理学研究
{\fs10}psychological human studies.

796
01:03:56,699 --> 01:03:57,982
是的 研究
{\fs10}Yes, the studies.

797
01:04:01,468 --> 01:04:03,953
旧医院档案可能在红室里
{\fs10}I think they put the files from the old hospital in the red room.

798
01:04:05,739 --> 01:04:06,723
红室
{\fs10}Red room?

799
01:04:08,142 --> 01:04:09,889
需要六周处理时间
{\fs10}Six weeks processing time.

800
01:04:09,976 --> 01:04:11,059
最多
{\fs10}At most.

801
01:04:12,179 --> 01:04:13,362
要笔吗
{\fs10}Need a pen?

802
01:04:18,903 --> 01:04:20,120
只能这样了
{\fs10}So much for that.

803
01:04:24,610 --> 01:04:25,591
来吧
{\fs10}Come on!

804
01:04:25,676 --> 01:04:26,993
不
{\fs10}No.

805
01:04:44,592 --> 01:04:46,172
我们别去红室
{\fs10}We are not going to the red room!

806
01:04:46,258 --> 01:04:47,708
不 我们要去红室
{\fs10}No, we are going to the red room.

807
01:04:47,794 --> 01:04:48,807
不 我不去 - 去
{\fs10}No, I'm not. - Yes.

808
01:04:48,896 --> 01:04:49,979
不 我不去
{\fs10}No. I'm not doing it.

809
01:04:52,232 --> 01:04:54,715
考夫曼医生 有电话
{\fs10}Dr. Kaufmann to telephone, please.

810
01:04:54,800 --> 01:04:56,714
考夫曼医生
{\fs10}Dr. Kaufmann.

811
01:04:56,802 --> 01:05:00,455
我跟你说了我的乱梦 我不想去
{\fs10}I told you about my dream. I don't want to go.

812
01:05:01,705 --> 01:05:03,956
那房间其实不是红色的 你没事
{\fs10}So, it isn't actually red. You're fine.

813
01:05:04,042 --> 01:05:06,230
<i>档案室 评估部 缩写RED</i>

814
01:05:07,778 --> 01:05:09,260
因为缩写为红室 好吗
{\fs10}It is called the red room, okay?

815
01:05:09,346 --> 01:05:11,464
谁说一定是红色的
{\fs10}Who said it had to be red?

816
01:05:12,350 --> 01:05:14,114
反正我不去
{\fs10}Uh-uh. Count me out.

817
01:05:14,617 --> 01:05:16,533
好 你就呆在这儿
{\fs10}Okay. Just... stay here.

818
01:05:18,656 --> 01:05:20,674
速度点 就没事的
{\fs10}Be quick. It'll be fine.

819
01:05:23,027 --> 01:05:24,643
别被逮住
{\fs10}Just don't get caught.

820
01:05:50,069 --> 01:05:51,895
<i>档案室(红室) 负二层</i>

821
01:06:08,097 --> 01:06:08,979
乔治·福尔曼
{\fs10}George Foreman.

822
01:06:09,066 --> 01:06:11,747
他将在73年成为世界冠军
{\fs10}He's going to be the world champion in '73.

823
01:06:11,833 --> 01:06:13,750
知道你去哪吗
{\fs10}Hey, you know where you're going?

824
01:06:18,340 --> 01:06:20,726
天啊 上帝 上帝 上帝
{\fs10}Oh, God. Oh, God, oh, God, oh, God.

825
01:06:23,211 --> 01:06:24,843
喂 你
{\fs10}Hey, you there.

826
01:06:25,311 --> 01:06:26,895
你不该在这
{\fs10}You're not supposed to be here.

827
01:06:26,984 --> 01:06:28,300
喂 站住
{\fs10}Hey! Stop!

828
01:06:38,955 --> 01:06:39,871
档案室(红室)
{\fs10}The R.E.D. room.

829
01:07:05,878 --> 01:07:08,294
入院档案 心理检查
{\fs10}Admittance records, psychological exams,

830
01:07:08,382 --> 01:07:09,964
她吃的
{\fs10}what she ate...

831
01:07:10,052 --> 01:07:12,235
全在 这儿
{\fs10}This is... everything.

832
01:07:13,390 --> 01:07:15,105
她被自己家人送入院的
{\fs10}She was admitted by her own family.

833
01:07:16,955 --> 01:07:22,642
这里说 她患有失色症-白化病
{\fs10}Says here that she was suffering from achromasia-albinism.

834
01:07:22,730 --> 01:07:24,980
他们把她关在地下室 因为她与众不同
{\fs10}They put her in her basement because she was different.

835
01:07:30,266 --> 01:07:32,652
她的监管医生是
{\fs10}Here, her supervising doctor was...

836
01:07:34,104 --> 01:07:35,654
以法连·贝洛斯医生
{\fs10}Dr. Ephraim Bellows.

837
01:07:36,304 --> 01:07:37,652
她的亲兄弟?
{\fs10}Her own brother?

838
01:07:38,107 --> 01:07:39,056
是
{\fs10}Yeah.

839
01:07:43,112 --> 01:07:46,161
天哪 他们折磨她
{\fs10}Jesus! They tortured her.

840
01:07:46,248 --> 01:07:47,697
看 电击
{\fs10}Look, electroshock,

841
01:07:47,784 --> 01:07:49,706
隔离疗法
{\fs10}isolation therapy,

842
01:07:50,152 --> 01:07:52,604
侧脑透热治疗
{\fs10}lateral cerebral diathermia treatment.

843
01:07:55,122 --> 01:07:56,205
这东西呢
{\fs10}What about this thing?

844
01:08:02,463 --> 01:08:03,747
这是什么
{\fs10}What is this?

845
01:08:06,934 --> 01:08:08,318
我以前见过
{\fs10}I've seen one of these before.

846
01:08:09,768 --> 01:08:11,084
是蜡筒唱片
{\fs10}It's a wax cylinder.

847
01:08:16,007 --> 01:08:18,660
比密纹唱片更早的唱片
{\fs10}They used them to make recordings before LPs.

848
01:08:22,277 --> 01:08:25,129
是不是能听到莎拉的声音
{\fs10}So, does that mean we're going to get to hear Sarah?

849
01:08:32,953 --> 01:08:34,226
他走这边
{\fs10}He went this way.

850
01:08:35,022 --> 01:08:36,073
拉警报
{\fs10}Sound the alarm!

851
01:08:41,528 --> 01:08:44,276
你现在要说实话
{\fs10}You're going to tell the truth now.

852
01:08:44,576 --> 01:08:46,226
是吗 莎拉
{\fs10}Aren't you, Sarah?

853
01:08:52,006 --> 01:08:55,258
我没有伤害孩子们
{\fs10}I didn't hurt the children.

854
01:08:57,543 --> 01:08:59,059
我没有
{\fs10}I didn't.

855
01:09:01,581 --> 01:09:02,463
以法连
{\fs10}Ephraim...

856
01:09:02,548 --> 01:09:06,646
那不是事实 对吗
{\fs10}That isn't the truth, is it?

857
01:09:06,951 --> 01:09:09,024
我没做
{\fs10}I didn't do it.

858
01:09:09,454 --> 01:09:10,902
我没伤害...
{\fs10}I didn't hurt...

859
01:09:15,258 --> 01:09:16,699
说实话 莎拉
{\fs10}Tell the truth, Sarah.

860
01:09:17,062 --> 01:09:18,774
我是你妹妹
{\fs10}I'm your sister...

861
01:09:18,864 --> 01:09:20,244
你毒死了那些孩子
{\fs10}You poisoned those children.

862
01:09:20,329 --> 01:09:22,347
没有
{\fs10}No. No.

863
01:09:23,199 --> 01:09:24,716
我试图
{\fs10}I tried...

864
01:09:25,501 --> 01:09:27,685
我试图拯救他们
{\fs10}I tried to save them.

865
01:09:29,601 --> 01:09:31,984
但没人听我的
{\fs10}But nobody listened.

866
01:09:32,972 --> 01:09:37,455
我不想他们受伤 但你不让我出去
{\fs10}I didn't want them hurt, but you wouldn't let me out.

867
01:09:37,542 --> 01:09:38,890
莎拉
{\fs10}Sarah...

868
01:09:43,897 --> 01:09:46,180
说实话
{\fs10}Tell the truth.

869
01:09:46,450 --> 01:09:47,936
她不知道自己做了什么
{\fs10}She doesn't know what she did.

870
01:09:48,919 --> 01:09:50,099
是水
{\fs10}It was the water.

871
01:09:50,187 --> 01:09:52,069
已经说过了 莎拉
{\fs10}We went over this, Sarah.

872
01:09:52,156 --> 01:09:53,310
水
{\fs10}The water.

873
01:09:53,812 --> 01:09:56,771
水没有问题
{\fs10}There's nothing wrong with the water.

874
01:09:57,293 --> 01:09:58,940
所以你才在这里
{\fs10}That's why you're here.

875
01:09:59,028 --> 01:10:00,149
造纸厂
{\fs10}The mill.

876
01:10:00,429 --> 01:10:03,178
是造纸厂的汞
{\fs10}It was the mercury from the mill.

877
01:10:03,266 --> 01:10:04,914
你毒了水...
{\fs10}You poisoned the wa...

878
01:10:08,371 --> 01:10:09,287
不是她
{\fs10}She didn't do it.

879
01:10:10,105 --> 01:10:11,021
是她的家人
{\fs10}It was her family.

880
01:10:14,611 --> 01:10:15,827
莎拉
{\fs10}Sarah,

881
01:10:16,612 --> 01:10:18,128
你还醒着吗
{\fs10}are you still here?

882
01:10:22,049 --> 01:10:23,365
我告诉你
{\fs10}I'll tell you.

883
01:10:24,988 --> 01:10:27,040
我会告诉你你想听的
{\fs10}I'll tell you what you want to hear.

884
01:10:28,053 --> 01:10:29,504
说吧
{\fs10}And what's that?

885
01:10:38,397 --> 01:10:41,782
查理梦见了红室
{\fs10}Charlie had a dream of a red room...

886
01:10:44,132 --> 01:10:45,146
查理
{\fs10}Charlie?

887
01:10:45,236 --> 01:10:46,217
就是档案室
{\fs10}The R.E.D. room.

888
01:10:46,301 --> 01:10:47,753
哪个查理
{\fs10}Charlie who?

889
01:10:48,504 --> 01:10:49,421
查克
{\fs10}Chuck.

890
01:10:50,374 --> 01:10:51,859
在他的梦里
{\fs10}In his dream,

891
01:10:53,043 --> 01:10:55,740
一个白脸女人
{\fs10}a woman with a pale face,

892
01:10:56,413 --> 01:10:58,035
黑眼女人
{\fs10}black eyes,

893
01:10:58,680 --> 01:11:04,624
一头长黑发 悄悄溜进他的房间
{\fs10}and long black hair slipped silently into his room.

894
01:11:05,353 --> 01:11:08,167
她俯身低声说
{\fs10}She leaned over and whispered,

895
01:11:08,689 --> 01:11:13,340
"在这邪恶之地
{\fs10}"This is an evil place.

896
01:11:13,427 --> 01:11:16,510
趁能跑 先跑"
{\fs10}"Run away while you still can."

897
01:11:32,206 --> 01:11:33,287
那可不妙
{\fs10}That's not good.

898
01:11:33,375 --> 01:11:34,359
查克
{\fs10}Chuck!

899
01:11:44,451 --> 01:11:45,435
救命
{\fs10}Help!

900
01:11:48,589 --> 01:11:50,106
救命 来人 救命
{\fs10}Help! Somebody, help!

901
01:12:37,430 --> 01:12:39,382
救命 来人 救命
{\fs10}Help! Please, somebody, help.

902
01:13:17,668 --> 01:13:19,117
救命 救命
{\fs10}Help. Help!

903
01:13:19,203 --> 01:13:20,701
有人 救命
{\fs10}Somebody, help!

904
01:13:21,272 --> 01:13:22,286
快
{\fs10}Come on!

905
01:14:15,819 --> 01:14:18,333
查克 查克 你在哪
{\fs10}Chuck! Chuck, where are you?

906
01:14:18,420 --> 01:14:19,336
查克
{\fs10}Chuck!

907
01:14:21,154 --> 01:14:22,136
他在哪
{\fs10}Where is he?

908
01:14:22,223 --> 01:14:23,435
他该在这里
{\fs10}He should be right here.

909
01:14:23,525 --> 01:14:25,676
查克 查克
{\fs10}Chuck? Chuck?

910
01:14:27,826 --> 01:14:28,976
查克
{\fs10}Chuck.

911
01:14:41,472 --> 01:14:44,458
你的小朋友呢
{\fs10}So, where's your little friend?

912
01:14:46,778 --> 01:14:49,696
继续68年选举之夜的新闻报道
{\fs10}News coverage of election night '68 continues.

913
01:14:52,248 --> 01:14:53,261
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella?

914
01:14:53,349 --> 01:14:54,071
爸爸
{\fs10}Dad.

915
01:14:54,751 --> 01:14:56,102
你没事吧 你在哪
{\fs10}Are you okay? Where are you?

916
01:14:57,419 --> 01:14:58,157
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella?

917
01:14:58,519 --> 01:15:00,501
恐怕我会死的 爸爸
{\fs10}I'm afraid I'm gonna die, Dad.

918
01:15:00,589 --> 01:15:02,637
亲爱的 别这么说
{\fs10}Aw, sweetie, don't say that.

919
01:15:02,724 --> 01:15:04,806
告诉我怎么了 我能做什么
{\fs10}Tell me what's wrong. Tell me what I can do.

920
01:15:04,892 --> 01:15:06,524
无能为力了
{\fs10}Can't do anything about it.

921
01:15:07,395 --> 01:15:09,377
我对此无能为力
{\fs10}I can't do anything about it.

922
01:15:09,464 --> 01:15:12,345
不 不 你得告诉我 亲爱的
{\fs10}No, no. You gotta help me out here, sweetie.

923
01:15:12,433 --> 01:15:15,083
你在哪 我马上就到
{\fs10}Tell me where you are. I will get there right away.

924
01:15:15,168 --> 01:15:17,151
我不在乎你经历了什么 快告诉我
{\fs10}I don't care what you're going through, just tell me, please.

925
01:15:17,239 --> 01:15:18,451
如果我失踪
{\fs10}If I go missing...

926
01:15:18,540 --> 01:15:19,591
失踪
{\fs10}Missing?

927
01:15:20,607 --> 01:15:22,024
如果你找不到我
{\fs10}If you can't find me...

928
01:15:22,710 --> 01:15:23,848
去哪儿找你
{\fs10}Find you where?

929
01:15:26,142 --> 01:15:26,890
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella?

930
01:15:27,635 --> 01:15:29,584
我没有离开你
{\fs10}I didn't leave you.

931
01:15:29,671 --> 01:15:31,393
我绝不会这样对你
{\fs10}I would never do that to you.

932
01:15:31,481 --> 01:15:33,896
我不明白你在说什么 丝黛拉 离开我?
{\fs10}I don't understand what you're talking about, Stella, leave me?

933
01:15:33,983 --> 01:15:34,689
你为什么要离开我
{\fs10}Why would you leave me?

934
01:15:34,774 --> 01:15:36,525
有人与你一起吗
{\fs10}Is someone there with you? Do...

935
01:15:42,525 --> 01:15:44,609
请听我说 亲爱的
{\fs10}Please just listen to me, sweetie.

936
01:15:45,918 --> 01:15:47,435
这不是你的错 丝黛拉
{\fs10}It's not your fault, Stella.

937
01:15:48,730 --> 01:15:50,481
她离开 不是你的错
{\fs10}It's not your fault she left.

938
01:15:52,268 --> 01:15:54,717
大家都怪我
{\fs10}Everyone said it was because of me.

939
01:15:54,802 --> 01:15:57,108
不 请听我说
{\fs10}Oh, no, please, please, please listen to me.

940
01:15:57,973 --> 01:15:59,734
她离开 不是你的错
{\fs10}It's not your fault she left.

941
01:16:00,675 --> 01:16:04,794
从来与你无关 是她的事
{\fs10}It was never, ever about you. It was about her.

942
01:16:07,648 --> 01:16:10,564
也许在内心深处 她只是
{\fs10}I don't know, somewhere deep down inside, she just...

943
01:16:11,751 --> 01:16:14,101
感觉被困住了什么的 我
{\fs10}felt trapped or something, I don't know, I...

944
01:16:15,420 --> 01:16:16,233
很复杂
{\fs10}It's complicated.

945
01:16:16,321 --> 01:16:17,836
我希望能有答案给你 亲爱的
{\fs10}I wish I had answers for you, sweetie,

946
01:16:17,924 --> 01:16:20,106
但我没有 我很抱歉
{\fs10}but I just don't and I'm so sorry.

947
01:16:23,529 --> 01:16:26,112
我爱你 爸爸 我得走了
{\fs10}I love you, Dad. I gotta go.

948
01:16:26,195 --> 01:16:28,475
这不是你的错 丝黛拉 请别挂电话 亲爱的
{\fs10}It's not your fault, Stella. Please don't hang up, sweetie.

949
01:16:28,563 --> 01:16:29,512
对不起 我得走了
{\fs10}I'm sorry, I'm sorry, I gotta go.

950
01:16:29,596 --> 01:16:30,411
我说 那不是你的...
{\fs10}I'm telling you, it wasn't your...

951
01:16:33,038 --> 01:16:35,515
那 你爸爸会来接你吗
{\fs10}So? Is your dad going to come pick you up?

952
01:16:38,372 --> 01:16:41,288
丝黛拉 怎么了
{\fs10}Oh, Stella, what's going on?

953
01:16:42,709 --> 01:16:44,762
最好你现在给我答案
{\fs10}I need answers from you right now.

954
01:16:45,445 --> 01:16:46,626
理解
{\fs10}Understand?

955
01:16:47,067 --> 01:16:50,531
理查德·尼克松占比43% 汉弗莱35%
{\fs10}Richard Nixon is still holding at 43 and Humphrey 35,

956
01:16:50,618 --> 01:16:52,550
但华莱士上升了1%
{\fs10}but, uh, Wallace has come up one point.

957
01:16:52,954 --> 01:16:54,175
那我的兵役呢
{\fs10}What about my call?

958
01:16:54,620 --> 01:16:57,336
制度不适用于逃兵役者
{\fs10}Rules don't apply to draft dodgers.

959
01:16:58,691 --> 01:17:00,139
你以为我发现不了吗
{\fs10}You think I wouldn't find out?

960
01:17:00,993 --> 01:17:03,265
雷蒙·莫拉莱斯
{\fs10}Ramon Morales.

961
01:17:03,996 --> 01:17:07,187
这样那样 你总得为国尽忠
{\fs10}You're gonna do your duty to this country one way or the other.

962
01:17:07,499 --> 01:17:10,450
如果你说说你失踪的朋友 我或可帮你
{\fs10}I can help you if you tell us about your missing friends.

963
01:17:10,535 --> 01:17:12,484
告诉你我们所知道的一切
{\fs10}Told you everything we know.

964
01:17:12,570 --> 01:17:13,621
是的
{\fs10}Oh, yeah, right.

965
01:17:14,607 --> 01:17:16,803
莎拉·贝洛斯的书
{\fs10}Sarah Bellows' book.

966
01:17:17,309 --> 01:17:21,327
故事自己写自己 竟然还能成真
{\fs10}The stories write themselves and it all comes alive.

967
01:17:22,680 --> 01:17:24,787
我们找不到任何尸体
{\fs10}We can't find any bodies.

968
01:17:25,244 --> 01:17:26,358
我知道
{\fs10}Yeah, I know.

969
01:17:27,715 --> 01:17:28,798
很难相信
{\fs10}It's hard to believe.

970
01:17:30,016 --> 01:17:32,164
我们在学校救了露西
{\fs10}We saved Ruth at school.

971
01:17:32,251 --> 01:17:34,204
我指的是 我们阻止她被杀
{\fs10}I mean, we stopped her from getting killed.

972
01:17:36,356 --> 01:17:37,669
露西·斯坦伯格
{\fs10}Ruth Steinberg?

973
01:17:37,991 --> 01:17:39,541
你说的是她吗
{\fs10}That's who you're talking about?

974
01:17:40,727 --> 01:17:41,807
你没救任何人
{\fs10}You didn't save anyone.

975
01:17:41,894 --> 01:17:44,879
她一辈子都得住精神病院
{\fs10}She's stuck in the nuthouse for the rest of her life.

976
01:17:46,331 --> 01:17:48,930
出去 丝黛拉 你可以走了
{\fs10}Get out of here, Stella. You're free to go.

977
01:17:49,300 --> 01:17:51,818
你比这个逃兵役者好多了
{\fs10}You're so much better than this draft dodger.

978
01:17:52,938 --> 01:17:54,855
你父亲会怎么说
{\fs10}Come on, what would your father say?

979
01:17:56,705 --> 01:17:57,821
我不会走的
{\fs10}I'm not leaving.

980
01:18:00,744 --> 01:18:02,293
既然你不去越南
{\fs10}Since you're not going to 'Nam,

981
01:18:02,380 --> 01:18:05,332
也许坐牢一晚 够你松嘴
{\fs10}maybe a night behind bars will loosen those lips of yours.

982
01:18:07,551 --> 01:18:09,365
来吧 霍布斯
{\fs10}Come on, Hobbs.

983
01:18:10,020 --> 01:18:11,870
回家 掏出那十块钱
{\fs10}Go home, dig out that 10 bucks

984
01:18:11,957 --> 01:18:14,079
尼克松获胜后 你会欠我的
{\fs10}you're gonna owe me when Nixon wins,

985
01:18:14,491 --> 01:18:15,804
我负责关门
{\fs10}and, uh, I'll close up here.

986
01:18:15,892 --> 01:18:16,942
好吧 晚安
{\fs10}All right, have a good night.

987
01:18:17,027 --> 01:18:18,511
晚安 爱情鸟
{\fs10}Nighty-night, lovebirds.

988
01:18:19,797 --> 01:18:21,248
我该告诉你的
{\fs10}I should've told you.

989
01:18:22,831 --> 01:18:24,346
你一定认为我是懦夫 但
{\fs10}You must think I'm a coward, but...

990
01:18:24,430 --> 01:18:25,882
我从没这么想
{\fs10}I would never think that.

991
01:18:34,607 --> 01:18:40,294
两个月前 他们七零八碎把我哥从越南运回
{\fs10}Two months ago they shipped my brother back from Vietnam in pieces.

992
01:18:41,078 --> 01:18:42,595
我很抱歉
{\fs10}I'm so sorry.

993
01:18:46,084 --> 01:18:48,367
上周我收到征兵通知
{\fs10}Last week when I got my draft notice,

994
01:18:50,920 --> 01:18:51,837
我做不到
{\fs10}I couldn't.

995
01:18:52,922 --> 01:18:54,238
他们是送你去死
{\fs10}They just send you there to die.

996
01:18:55,992 --> 01:18:57,242
如果书读出我
{\fs10}If the book reads me,

997
01:18:59,316 --> 01:19:00,801
我害怕它要读出什么
{\fs10}I'm afraid what it's going to say.

998
01:19:28,385 --> 01:19:29,599
给你 孩子
{\fs10}There you go, boy.

999
01:19:30,119 --> 01:19:31,505
很好吧
{\fs10}Yeah, that's good, huh?

1000
01:19:39,930 --> 01:19:42,415
"我系坚强行者"
{\fs10}"Me Tie Dough-ty Walker"?

1001
01:19:53,440 --> 01:19:55,893
谁想出的恶心东西
{\fs10}Who came up with all this sick stuff?

1002
01:19:57,544 --> 01:19:58,796
是你吗 丝黛拉
{\fs10}Is this you, Stella?

1003
01:20:00,013 --> 01:20:02,194
我们没写故事
{\fs10}We didn't write the stories.

1004
01:20:39,582 --> 01:20:40,247
狗狗
{\fs10}Trigger?

1005
01:20:43,819 --> 01:20:45,002
等等 又有新故事了吗
{\fs10}Wait, is there another story?

1006
01:20:46,187 --> 01:20:47,501
求你了 放我们出去
{\fs10}Please, you have to let us out!

1007
01:20:47,587 --> 01:20:48,569
如果又有新故事
{\fs10}Okay, if there's another story,

1008
01:20:48,656 --> 01:20:50,371
我们都会有危险
{\fs10}we are all gonna be in danger.

1009
01:20:53,459 --> 01:20:54,938
告诉我们发生了什么
{\fs10}Tell us what's happening!

1010
01:20:55,027 --> 01:20:56,610
是什么故事
{\fs10}What's the story?

1011
01:21:01,565 --> 01:21:02,814
请听我说 好吗
{\fs10}Please just listen to me, okay?

1012
01:21:02,902 --> 01:21:04,292
我们都要死了
{\fs10}We're all going to die.

1013
01:21:19,920 --> 01:21:21,241
轮到我了
{\fs10}It's my turn.

1014
01:21:21,483 --> 01:21:23,577
故事怎么说的
{\fs10}Okay, what happens in the story?

1015
01:21:24,551 --> 01:21:26,740
把书里的名字告诉我
{\fs10}Just tell me which name is in the book.

1016
01:21:27,923 --> 01:21:28,743
雷蒙
{\fs10}Ramon.

1017
01:21:39,866 --> 01:21:41,423
这是篝火故事
{\fs10}It's a campfire story.

1018
01:21:42,085 --> 01:21:43,291
曾经吓坏我
{\fs10}It used to scare me to death.

1019
01:21:48,775 --> 01:21:50,054
猛鬼来了
{\fs10}The Jangly Man is coming.

1020
01:21:50,142 --> 01:21:51,124
他会带我去
{\fs10}He's going to take me...

1021
01:21:51,210 --> 01:21:52,390
怎么了
{\fs10}What's going on?

1022
01:21:52,743 --> 01:21:54,393
他会说的 听好了
{\fs10}He's going to say it. Listen.

1023
01:22:01,886 --> 01:22:05,869
我系坚强行者
{\fs10}Me tie dough-ty walker!

1024
01:22:05,956 --> 01:22:07,506
你耍我吗
{\fs10}Are you shitting me?

1025
01:22:28,630 --> 01:22:30,446
请让我们出去
{\fs10}Please, just let us out, please!

1026
01:23:03,872 --> 01:23:07,058
我系坚强行者
{\fs10}Me tie dough-ty walker!

1027
01:23:24,822 --> 01:23:26,407
雷蒙
{\fs10}Ramon!

1028
01:23:29,092 --> 01:23:31,105
雷蒙
{\fs10}Ramon.

1029
01:23:31,194 --> 01:23:32,843
天哪 雷蒙
{\fs10}Oh, my God, Ramon.

1030
01:23:32,930 --> 01:23:33,981
天哪 那是什么
{\fs10}Oh, my God, what is that?

1031
01:23:37,601 --> 01:23:40,553
救命 有人听到我吗
{\fs10}Help. Help, please. Can someone hear me?

1032
01:23:46,675 --> 01:23:47,887
钥匙
{\fs10}Keys.

1033
01:23:47,976 --> 01:23:48,892
快点
{\fs10}Hurry!

1034
01:24:05,793 --> 01:24:06,809
懦夫
{\fs10}Coward!

1035
01:24:09,997 --> 01:24:11,482
我拿到钥匙了
{\fs10}I got the keys.

1036
01:24:13,067 --> 01:24:14,819
拜托
{\fs10}Come on, come on, come on, come on.

1037
01:24:18,304 --> 01:24:19,455
懦夫
{\fs10}Coward!

1038
01:24:21,803 --> 01:24:23,486
跑啊
{\fs10}Run! Go, go, go!

1039
01:24:38,866 --> 01:24:40,242
你还等什么
{\fs10}What are you waiting for?

1040
01:24:41,165 --> 01:24:42,162
去老屋
{\fs10}Go to the house.

1041
01:24:42,864 --> 01:24:44,012
告诉她真相
{\fs10}Tell her the truth.

1042
01:24:44,100 --> 01:24:45,380
那怪物会跟着我
{\fs10}That thing will follow me.

1043
01:24:45,468 --> 01:24:47,318
但故事每次都成真
{\fs10}But the stories come true every time.

1044
01:24:47,716 --> 01:24:48,751
那你最好跑快
{\fs10}Then you better run fast.

1045
01:24:49,763 --> 01:24:51,756
制止她 就等于制止一切
{\fs10}Stop her and you'll stop this.

1046
01:26:36,162 --> 01:26:37,511
莎拉
{\fs10}Sarah!

1047
01:26:37,598 --> 01:26:39,512
你能听到我吗
{\fs10}Can you hear me?

1048
01:26:39,699 --> 01:26:42,949
你去死 你必须停讲故事
{\fs10}God damn you! You have to stop telling these stories!

1049
01:26:43,037 --> 01:26:45,052
我们没对不起你
{\fs10}We didn't do anything to you!

1050
01:26:45,139 --> 01:26:47,620
我们只想帮你 我们知你无辜
{\fs10}We just want to help you! We know you're innocent!

1051
01:26:47,707 --> 01:26:49,622
我们知你没毒死孩子
{\fs10}We know you didn't poison the kids!

1052
01:26:49,710 --> 01:26:52,963
但请你停讲故事
{\fs10}But, please, you just have to stop telling the stories!

1053
01:27:47,992 --> 01:27:48,948
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella!

1054
01:27:49,427 --> 01:27:50,284
你在哪
{\fs10}Where are you?

1055
01:27:57,266 --> 01:27:58,250
不不不
{\fs10}No, no, no, no.

1056
01:27:59,401 --> 01:28:00,382
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella.

1057
01:28:08,036 --> 01:28:08,993
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella!

1058
01:28:21,318 --> 01:28:22,057
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Hey, Stella!

1059
01:28:27,458 --> 01:28:28,940
她又出房间了
{\fs10}She's out of her room again.

1060
01:28:29,025 --> 01:28:31,010
小子们 莎拉出来了
{\fs10}Boys? Sarah's out!

1061
01:28:31,763 --> 01:28:33,279
马上找到她
{\fs10}Find her now!

1062
01:28:34,363 --> 01:28:35,280
莎拉
{\fs10}Sarah!

1063
01:28:43,974 --> 01:28:44,871
莎拉
{\fs10}Sarah!

1064
01:28:47,711 --> 01:28:49,793
交给我 哈罗德
{\fs10}You leave that to me, Harold.

1065
01:28:53,514 --> 01:28:54,588
莎拉
{\fs10}Sarah!

1066
01:28:56,751 --> 01:28:58,268
莎拉 你在哪
{\fs10}Sarah, where are you?

1067
01:29:06,095 --> 01:29:07,061
莎拉
{\fs10}Sarah!

1068
01:29:20,668 --> 01:29:22,382
我听见她了
{\fs10}I hear her.

1069
01:29:30,846 --> 01:29:32,362
她在这
{\fs10}She's here!

1070
01:29:34,215 --> 01:29:35,932
她在这
{\fs10}She's in here!

1071
01:29:54,835 --> 01:29:55,951
莎拉
{\fs10}Sarah!

1072
01:29:58,472 --> 01:29:59,422
你在哪
{\fs10}Where are you?

1073
01:30:06,244 --> 01:30:07,160
卢卢
{\fs10}Lou Lou.

1074
01:30:24,840 --> 01:30:25,537
你看到莎拉了吗
{\fs10}Did you see Sarah?

1075
01:30:25,628 --> 01:30:26,676
没有 夫人
{\fs10}No, ma'am.

1076
01:30:26,760 --> 01:30:27,742
她在撒谎
{\fs10}She's lying.

1077
01:30:27,829 --> 01:30:31,086
你没在谎吧 卢卢
{\fs10}You wouldn't lie, Lou Lou?

1078
01:30:31,499 --> 01:30:32,480
没有 夫人
{\fs10}No, ma'am.

1079
01:30:32,565 --> 01:30:33,746
不 我没看到莎拉
{\fs10}No, I didn't see Sarah.

1080
01:30:33,836 --> 01:30:35,817
不 贝洛斯先生 不
{\fs10}No, Mr. Bellows, please, no!

1081
01:30:35,903 --> 01:30:37,484
求你了 不
{\fs10}Please, no!

1082
01:31:08,231 --> 01:31:09,182
你不躲掉我们
{\fs10}You can't hide from us.

1083
01:31:09,867 --> 01:31:10,848
抓到你了
{\fs10}Got you!

1084
01:31:10,935 --> 01:31:13,043
不 不
{\fs10}No! No!

1085
01:31:13,435 --> 01:31:15,517
救我
{\fs10}Help me! Help me!

1086
01:31:15,605 --> 01:31:17,295
救我 - 丝黛拉
{\fs10}Help me! - Stella!

1087
01:31:17,641 --> 01:31:20,554
请救救我
{\fs10}Please! Help me!

1088
01:31:20,638 --> 01:31:22,553
救我 - 她总向别人提到水
{\fs10}Please, help me! - She's been telling everyone about the water.

1089
01:31:22,641 --> 01:31:23,622
拿她怎么办
{\fs10}What should we do with her?

1090
01:31:23,709 --> 01:31:25,024
救我
{\fs10}Somebody, help me, please.

1091
01:31:25,112 --> 01:31:26,359
闭上你的丑嘴 否则我们替你闭嘴
{\fs10}You're going to shut your ugly mouth or we're going to shut it for you.

1092
01:31:26,445 --> 01:31:28,135
救我
{\fs10}Please, help me!

1093
01:31:28,580 --> 01:31:31,333
救我
{\fs10}Help me, please!

1094
01:31:35,955 --> 01:31:37,535
你哪儿来哪儿去
{\fs10}Going back where you belong.

1095
01:31:37,622 --> 01:31:39,370
救我
{\fs10}Help me, please.

1096
01:31:39,457 --> 01:31:41,410
安静 否则有你好看
{\fs10}Be quiet or you know what you'll get.

1097
01:31:43,195 --> 01:31:45,809
求你们 我不是莎拉
{\fs10}Please. I'm not Sarah. Please!

1098
01:31:45,897 --> 01:31:48,149
拜托让我走
{\fs10}Please let me go. Please...

1099
01:31:48,767 --> 01:31:50,251
让我走
{\fs10}Let me go.

1100
01:31:51,569 --> 01:31:52,716
请别关我在这
{\fs10}Please, don't put me in here.

1101
01:31:52,803 --> 01:31:54,884
你再敢 送你去救济院
{\fs10}Try this again and we'll send you to the asylum.

1102
01:31:54,970 --> 01:31:57,820
等等 求你们
{\fs10}Please. Wait! Please?

1103
01:31:57,908 --> 01:31:59,756
你就该呆在你房里
{\fs10}You should have stayed in your room.

1104
01:31:59,841 --> 01:32:02,325
求你们
{\fs10}Please. Please. Please.

1105
01:32:02,413 --> 01:32:03,426
不是我干的
{\fs10}I didn't do it.

1106
01:32:03,514 --> 01:32:05,363
你不配有光
{\fs10}You don't deserve the light.

1107
01:32:05,449 --> 01:32:06,500
不
{\fs10}No!

1108
01:32:08,282 --> 01:32:10,766
我告诉你们
{\fs10}I'm telling you, I'm telling you,

1109
01:32:10,854 --> 01:32:12,570
我不是莎拉
{\fs10}I'm not Sarah.

1110
01:32:13,889 --> 01:32:15,636
求你们
{\fs10}Please.

1111
01:33:23,948 --> 01:33:25,463
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella...

1112
01:33:40,763 --> 01:33:44,714
我有新故事 只给你
{\fs10}I have another story just for you.

1113
01:33:51,472 --> 01:33:52,456
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella,

1114
01:33:54,607 --> 01:33:57,525
如果你能听到我 无论你在哪
{\fs10}if you can hear me, wherever you are,

1115
01:33:58,644 --> 01:34:00,529
告诉她真相
{\fs10}tell her the truth.

1116
01:34:06,686 --> 01:34:07,435
不
{\fs10}No.

1117
01:34:10,128 --> 01:34:12,513
该你听故事了 莎拉
{\fs10}It's time that you hear a story, Sarah.

1118
01:34:16,996 --> 01:34:18,244
你是受害者
{\fs10}You were a victim.

1119
01:34:19,994 --> 01:34:22,511
现在你成了怪物
{\fs10}Now you've turned into a monster.

1120
01:34:23,964 --> 01:34:26,282
成了他们口中的你
{\fs10}The one that they said you were.

1121
01:34:35,445 --> 01:34:36,360
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella.

1122
01:34:37,946 --> 01:34:39,629
你带走了我的朋友们
{\fs10}You took my friends.

1123
01:34:41,481 --> 01:34:43,632
我最爱的两个人
{\fs10}Two of the people that I love most.

1124
01:34:52,490 --> 01:34:53,774
雷蒙
{\fs10}Ramon!

1125
01:34:55,728 --> 01:34:56,808
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella!

1126
01:34:58,496 --> 01:34:59,948
你也要带走他吗
{\fs10}Are you going to take him, too?

1127
01:35:01,405 --> 01:35:03,281
你家人对你的所为
{\fs10}What your family did to you,

1128
01:35:04,434 --> 01:35:05,908
对你的所言 罪在他们
{\fs10}what they said, that's on them.

1129
01:35:07,906 --> 01:35:09,357
但你的所为
{\fs10}But what you do,

1130
01:35:11,876 --> 01:35:13,526
罪在你 莎拉
{\fs10}this is on you, Sarah.

1131
01:35:17,184 --> 01:35:18,369
你是原罪
{\fs10}It's all on you.

1132
01:35:26,751 --> 01:35:28,367
我会叙述你的故事
{\fs10}I'll tell your story.

1133
01:35:30,990 --> 01:35:33,306
真实版的故事 我实话实说
{\fs10}The real story, I'll tell the truth.

1134
01:35:36,995 --> 01:35:37,946
但愤怒
{\fs10}But the rage,

1135
01:35:39,099 --> 01:35:41,584
你的愤怒必须停 莎拉
{\fs10}the rage has to stop, Sarah.

1136
01:36:02,820 --> 01:36:04,336
用你的血来写
{\fs10}Use your blood.

1137
01:36:27,172 --> 01:36:30,022
莎拉·贝洛斯是无辜的
{\fs10}Sarah Bellows was innocent.

1138
01:36:30,507 --> 01:36:32,592
她知道真相
{\fs10}She knew the truth,

1139
01:36:33,777 --> 01:36:35,360
并试图阻止他们
{\fs10}and tried to stop them.

1140
01:36:35,713 --> 01:36:36,629
她很勇敢
{\fs10}She was brave.

1141
01:36:37,581 --> 01:36:42,326
她被亲人伤害摧毁
{\fs10}She was harmed and destroyed by her own family.

1142
01:36:42,851 --> 01:36:44,635
被其贪婪
{\fs10}By their greed,

1143
01:36:45,522 --> 01:36:46,938
被其谎言
{\fs10}and their lies

1144
01:36:47,757 --> 01:36:49,007
被其罪过
{\fs10}and their sins.

1145
01:36:51,693 --> 01:36:52,944
我来叙述你的故事
{\fs10}I'll tell your story.

1146
01:36:58,501 --> 01:36:59,784
你可以解脱了
{\fs10}You can let it go.

1147
01:37:02,136 --> 01:37:03,587
解脱吧 莎拉
{\fs10}You can let it go, Sarah.

1148
01:37:49,011 --> 01:37:50,526
故事伤人
{\fs10}Stories hurt.

1149
01:37:51,143 --> 01:37:52,661
故事治人
{\fs10}Stories heal.

1150
01:37:56,582 --> 01:37:59,869
如果故事一再重复 它们会成真
{\fs10}If we repeat them often enough, they become real.

1151
01:38:00,822 --> 01:38:02,374
它们有这种力量
{\fs10}They have that power.

1152
01:38:06,158 --> 01:38:07,707
故事造就了我们
{\fs10}They make us who we are.

1153
01:38:07,793 --> 01:38:08,775
丝黛拉
{\fs10}Stella.

1154
01:38:08,861 --> 01:38:10,644
我很高兴你没事
{\fs10}I'm just so happy you're okay.

1155
01:38:23,303 --> 01:38:26,456
如果我从莎拉那里学到了什么
{\fs10}And if there's anything I learned from Sarah,

1156
01:38:28,144 --> 01:38:29,995
那就是永不放弃
{\fs10}it's to never give up.

1157
01:38:32,613 --> 01:38:35,800
我按照承诺 精准复述了莎拉的故事
{\fs10}I told Sarah's story exactly as I promised.

1158
01:38:37,585 --> 01:38:42,329
我写道: 一个苍白孤独的姑娘 在黑暗中写故事
{\fs10}I wrote about the pale, lonely girl who wrote stories in the dark.

1159
01:38:43,658 --> 01:38:46,877
她的家人把她变成怪物
{\fs10}And how she was turned into a monster by her family.

1160
01:38:50,129 --> 01:38:53,355
有人信我 大多数不信我
{\fs10}Some people believed me. Most didn't.

1161
01:38:53,832 --> 01:38:55,147
因为 如同莎拉
{\fs10}Because, like Sarah,

1162
01:38:55,599 --> 01:38:59,751
我孤女一枚 会讲恐怖故事
{\fs10}I was a lonely girl who knew how to tell a good creepy story.

1163
01:39:07,012 --> 01:39:07,929
写信给我
{\fs10}Write me?

1164
01:39:20,287 --> 01:39:21,471
每天
{\fs10}Every day.

1165
01:39:23,156 --> 01:39:24,172
再见
{\fs10}See you around.

1166
01:39:28,896 --> 01:39:30,007
你叫什么 孩子
{\fs10}What's your name, kid?

1167
01:39:30,096 --> 01:39:31,112
雷蒙·莫拉莱斯
{\fs10}Ramon Morales.

1168
01:39:35,867 --> 01:39:38,051
故事教我们关爱
{\fs10}Stories can teach us to care.

1169
01:39:41,708 --> 01:39:44,895
故事令我们勇敢承认 人需要彼此
{\fs10}They make us brave enough to admit that we need each other.

1170
01:39:46,045 --> 01:39:48,630
给我们一个家 可以回
{\fs10}Give us a home to go back to.

1171
01:40:01,159 --> 01:40:04,484
查克和奥吉仍失踪
{\fs10}Chuck and Auggie are still gone,

1172
01:40:05,261 --> 01:40:08,677
但我有办法带回他们
{\fs10}but I know there is a way to bring them back

1173
01:40:08,766 --> 01:40:10,517
秘密就在书里
{\fs10}and that the secret is in the book.

1174
01:40:11,900 --> 01:40:13,984
我们不会收手
{\fs10}And we won't stop...

1175
01:40:16,100 --> 01:40:17,885
除非找到他们
{\fs10}until we find them.



